<br>
The first time I ever met Fuvi was on Vazaelle, where he was playing a high elf cleric.<br>
<br>
My guild was raiding Mistmoore, and all our clerics managed to go linkdead.  Total Wipeout.  Fuvi (Cure at the time) was in the neighborhood, and took about an hour out of his day to resurrect my entire guild.<br>
<br>
Here on FV, was raiding Mistmoore here with the guild I was in (Starspun).  We made it to the castle and got our asses trained back out.  By the time we made it back to the castle again, too many people had to leave for us to have a raiding party.  Fuvi was nearby, and had Mistmoore faction, so he waltzed into the Castle and pulled out werewolves, gypsies, and all other kinds of fun stuff out to the courtyard for us to kill.  We ended up w/ talon's for Mixxi &amp; someone else's crafted Breastplate, lutes for Mine and someone else's lambent BP, blood spirits for our rogues burning rapiers, and some other goodies.  It turned a day that might have ended on a sour note into a great one.<br>
<br>
Rather than roll up an alt to do quests that went TLC, he involved lower level members of the community to do the quests for him for payment, mercenary style.  Call it lazy if ya want, but it involved a lot of people within the community and gave them access to some neat treasures they might not have otherwise had the time or experience to gain.<br>
<br>
I'm sure some individual people might have had their problems with him (Kurley, Krit/Restoria, etc), and he might even have instigated those problems, but I'm seein a lot of people trying to demonize him as some kind of psycopath.  I've had a little interaction with him on Vazaelle, and a ton here, and it's all been positive.  That's not to say he's always a great guy, I don't stalk him to see what he does when I'm around, but I think there's a lot of bringing up what amounts to personal disputes between him &amp; certain individuals as a means of trying to distract from other issues being discussed (Sleepers or whatever).<br>
<br>
