In fact, I did not inform anyone of the email until your behavior in-guild was escalating to the point that the officers were forced to talk about you.  Repudiate that comment all you want.  Regardless, that relevant morsel of information was discussed with a few people in the officer circle, as were other, unrelated instances of your behavior that some guild members and some guild officers didn't really dig.  Likewise, two RL friends who play EQ were informed of this (do the math), however I can't say that it really changed their opinion of you anyways.<br>
<br>
That was months ago and I haven't played EQ, haven't had any involvement in FnF politics, nor really posted on these boards, except for the occassional picture or other nonesense.<br>
<br>
Thus, while perhaps you'd like to find some satisfaction in the thought of me spending all of this past time, developing some Machiavellian plan to &quot;take you down&quot;, again you're sadly mistaken.  I was pretty clear in my goodbye to the guild how I wanted to leave, without being overly specific in the details - and no Fuvi, you were not the only reason I lost my love for the game.  You'll also recall I didn't sling a pile of mud at you or anyone else.  Did I come to the public boards and post &quot;truthful&quot; information about someone I didn't really care for?  Did I use an excuse that I was looking out for the best interests of others on the server?  Negative to both...but check your own recent motives &quot;truthfully&quot;.<br>
<br>
Flash forward to recently, where the instance of said email was used by someone to prove a point in a moment of emotionalism.  Was I happy that Kzan brought it up?  No, as it was a dated issue, he had no right to bring it up publicly, and he could have used any number of other examples to try to prove his point.  In fact, Kzan can attest to how displeased I was to have my name brought into this whole, stupid drama.<br>
<br>
However, after reading your post on this, I full and well had the right to respond.  You've patted yourself on the back as enjoying the cause and effect of psychology and manipulation and branded yourself &quot;good at it for specific reasons&quot;.  <br>
<br>
The way you presented that email and Bako's Sleeper post, were of course accurate in their elements (those are indeed the quotes and words used in those instances), however not truthful, except from your point of view, for your purpose.  Well there are different points of view of any set of facts, and the truth of a situation is merely a given perspective of the facts, which always risks exposure to manipulation.  Feel free to repudiate your affinity for manipulation and social psychology.<br>
<br>
So you didn't like what I posted?  Obviously it bothered you enough to repost after I simply stated the truth and in fact said a number of non-infammatory things that you should read more carefully.  However if what I posted, which you'<br>
re welcome to challenge as untruthful, bothered you enough to attempt to spin it into something less valid (the tale of the co-op and the doggy poo), then maybe make a Darwinian leap in your ability to empathize, and come to the realization that being an asshole is going to garner you a few enemies.<br>
<br>
And that, not the email that we're discussing, is what lead to your deguilding.  If you believe that I revived a recent campaign to evict Fuvi and his discontinent dog from the coop, then you need to look elsewhere.<br>
<br>
Now onto some of your content above:<br>
<br>
&quot;I knew the email didn't cause a problem before Kurley lied in his reply to me and made an issue of it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Right...and where did I lie about the effect that email had on my opinion of you.  At the very least, it was an example of a poor sense of humor (read, that was like the 2nd email you sent me), and at the very worst it was an example of something that a creep would do.  However that particular email was by no means the linchpin in my overall opinion of you.  It was just a reaffirming piece of the picture, that was your consistent pattern of comments and actions towards others, which you should well know I have plenty of examples of.<br>
<br>
&quot;There was my failsafe, you see if she considers the anonymous email meaningless, there is nothing to apologize for, if she is willing to attack Kurley about it it's also worth replying to, something she didn't do.&quot;<br>
<br>
Here is an equally absurd interpretation.  If I mess with the brakelines of your car, and you don't run into a situation where you're required to slam on your breaks, then it was harmless and I have nothing to apologize for.  Your assumption that something worth attacking someone for is something worth replying to is also just that, an assumption and holds no validity except in your mind - scour psychology texts all you want, there is no Litmus test for what you've accepted as a true failsafe.<br>
<br>
&quot;The email I did send didn't have ANY genuine chance at disruption, either I didn't want it to be disruptive or I'm just not clever enough to figure out how to send a potentially disruptive email.&quot;<br>
<br>
Clearly, your example of a true attempt at a disruptive email (as presented above in your post) would have a better chance at achieving it's goal.  Also, it would be much harder to play damage control on an email like that as well, wouldn't it?  I don't think I've ever questioned your intelligence and knack for subtlety.<br>
<br>
At this point, it's pretty much just you and me reading all of this tripe I would think.  So why don't I answer the flat question of whether or not I thought you meant harm with that email.<br>
<br>
As stated before, I thought it was an odd thing to do, which is a pretty reasonable reaction.  That can be countered by questioning my sense of humor, however anyone who has spent any time around me in EQ, knows different.<br>
<br>
It's only after observing aspects - I'm not painting you entirely with this brush - of your interaction with the guild we belonged to and certain members, clear instances of practiced manipulation (again, feel free to refute), and the venemous disdain you practiced against specific members of our guild, did I reconsider your original intention.<br>
<br>
You constantly acknowledge that you can be an asshole - I'm qualifying by saying can be, rather than are, as I know different.  You also acknowledge that you enjoy psychology, stimulation and outcome.  You know you have used manipulation to prove your points - the &quot;withholding loot&quot; issue is well known to those involved.  You know that I am not the only one to have had a negative reaction to the way you conduct yourself at times.  Feel free to repudiate any of the above.<br>
<br>
If you take all of those knowns together, it would not be inconsistent behavior, as observed.  But in truth, I'll never know the &quot;truth&quot;, nor do I really care other than to discuss semantics.  I had considered the email, and the encompassing issue &quot;dead and burried&quot; until all of this was dragged out - neither by you or me - and I exercised my right to convey my version of the &quot;truth&quot; since, in a far off way, it involved me - in EQ at any rate.<br>
<br>
&quot;in fact this post is a lot of fun, pointing out the self-destructive behavior of someone who made so much effort to pull me down brings a smile to my face, because indeed I am an @sshole and a happy one at that.&quot;<br>
<br>
It IS a fun diversion in a way.  But you need to stop fooling yourself about the self-destruction and singular effort to &quot;pull you down&quot; that brings the smile to your face.  Again, I didn't bring this whole topic to light, and I did not have any involvement in your recent ejection from FnF - other than the fact that I was involved in events that transpired months ago.  You freely admit that you can piss people off, that you're an @sshole and/or a prick when you want to be, so why focus on the fact that I came to regard you as one when it's a foregone accepted that some others have come to that conclusion as well. <br>
<br>
By attempting to pin your &quot;villification&quot; and deguilding from FnF on me, or thinking that I had to &quot;prove what an @sshole you are&quot; to others, when that conclusion was drawn by the respective persons independently of me, you aren't facing the truth, and I thought truth &gt; all.  Really, it's just a political maneuver akin to blaming the prior administration.<br>
<br>
I suggest you reread my previous posts in this thread to actually see the tone at which I'm writing this and what I was actually saying.<br>
<br>
You say &quot;I have no problem accepting consequences for my actions.&quot; but your post above just serves to hobble that statement.  When you act nice to certain people, they will like you, when you act like an @ss to certain people, the recipients of that behavior and those observing it may or may not like you.<br>
<br>
At any rate, enjoy playing EQ and enjoy being an @sshole as you acquiese that it makes you happy, but just learn to accept that it may not float everyone's boat.  As for the email, I'm stating for the 2nd time in this thread that it's a dead fricking horse, and we're just batting around perceived intentions and interpretations for arguement's sake.<br>
<br>
And believe me when I say that it's perfectly okay and possible to disagree, even conflict, and live at peace. <br>
